<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 6:44PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Morgan County
through 715 PM MDT...
At 644 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Weldona, or 7 miles northwest of Fort Morgan, moving
southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree branches and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Brush, Log Lane Village, Hillrose, Gary, Antelope
Springs, Weldona, Adena, Twelve-Mile Corner, Snyder and Adena School.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
